Enhance the Workflow Agent and Automation Command Center with an AI Operational Memory system.

Important constraints:
- Do not change the existing UI design system.
- Preserve the current Command Center layout.
- Preserve AiBox style from the Agent Detail page.
- Do not modify Watch Center UI.

The goal is to allow the Workflow Agent to understand the entire automation environment instead of only the currently open workflow.

---

SECTION 1 — ADD AI SYSTEM INSIGHTS PANEL

Inside the Automation Command Center add a new panel above Optimization Opportunities.

Title:
AI System Insights

This panel should highlight the most important operational observations.

Examples:

Approval bottleneck detected across 3 workflows  
Slack notification failures increasing in the past 24 hours  
Asset Discovery workflow runs slower than average

Each insight should include:

Affected workflows  
Impact description  
Suggested improvement

Actions:
View Workflows  
Ask AI  
Apply Fix

---

SECTION 2 — PRIORITIZE OPTIMIZATION OPPORTUNITIES

Improve the Optimization Opportunities section by grouping suggestions.

Groups:

Reliability Improvements  
Performance Improvements  
Governance Improvements

Example:

Reliability Improvements
Add retry logic to Slack notifications

Performance Improvements
Replace polling trigger with scheduled run

Governance Improvements
Add audit logging for compliance workflows

This grouping improves scanability and actionability.

---

SECTION 3 — ADD AI PRIORITY INDICATOR

Inside the Command Center show a small priority badge for issues.

Priority levels:

High  
Medium  
Low

Example:

High Priority
Approval bottleneck in Vulnerability Remediation Flow

Medium Priority
Slack notification retries recommended

Low Priority
Polling trigger replacement suggestion

