SECTION 5 — ADD AI WORKFLOW HEALTH RANKING

Inside the Command Center introduce a compact workflow health ranking.

Example:

Workflow Health

Critical Alert Auto-Response — Healthy  
Vulnerability Remediation Flow — Warning  
Risk Escalation Pipeline — Critical

This ranking should be based on:

failure rate  
delays  
AI-detected issues

---

SECTION 6 — IMPROVE WORKFLOW AGENT CONTEXT

When the Workflow Agent is opened while viewing a workflow, the agent must automatically understand:

current workflow  
workflow steps  
run history  
detected issues

This allows commands like:

Optimize this workflow  
Explain this workflow  
Why does this step fail?  
Simulate failure scenario

The AI should not require manual selection.

---

SECTION 7 — IMPROVE EMPTY WORKFLOW CREATION SCREEN

When creating a new workflow, improve the empty state.

Instead of showing only a placeholder, show suggested starting triggers:

Watch Center Alert  
Vulnerability Detected  
Asset Discovered  
Scheduled Workflow  
Manual Trigger

These should appear as clickable options.

---

SECTION 8 — ADD AI REASONING EXPANDER

Inside AI Understanding blocks add an expandable reasoning section.

Example:

AI Understanding
Trigger — Watch Center Critical Alert
Action — Create Investigation Case

Show Reasoning

Reasoning explains why these steps were chosen.

This improves transparency.

---

SECTION 9 — FINAL RESULT

After this improvement:

The Workflow Agent becomes aware of the entire automation environment.

Users can ask operational questions about automation performance.

Command Center becomes a true AI-driven automation control surface rather than just a dashboard.